# SvelteKit Static Site Project Structure

This is a static SvelteKit application deployed to Cloudflare Pages with Tailwind CSS.

## Core Architecture
- **Framework**: SvelteKit 2.x with static adapter for Cloudflare Pages
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.x with Vite plugin integration
- **TypeScript**: Full TypeScript support with strict configuration
- **Deployment**: Cloudflare Pages with Wrangler CLI
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (preferred for this project)

## Key Files & Directories
- [svelte.config.js](mdc:svelte.config.js) - SvelteKit configuration with Cloudflare adapter
- [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts) - Vite configuration with Tailwind CSS plugin
- [wrangler.jsonc](mdc:wrangler.jsonc) - Cloudflare Pages deployment configuration
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and deployment scripts
- [src/routes/](mdc:src/routes/) - SvelteKit routes and pages
- [src/lib/](mdc:src/lib/) - Reusable components and utilities
- [src/app.css](mdc:src/app.css) - Global styles and Tailwind directives
- [static/](mdc:static/) - Static assets served directly

## Build & Deploy Process
1. `pnpm run build` - Builds static site to `.svelte-kit/cloudflare`
2. `pnpm run deploy` - Deploys to Cloudflare Pages using Wrangler
3. `pnpm run preview` - Local preview with Cloudflare Pages dev server

## Development Commands
- `pnpm dev` - Development server
- `pnpm run check` - Type checking
- `pnpm run lint` - ESLint
- `pnpm run cf-typegen` - Generate Cloudflare types